About Our County

Dedicated to sharing a rich heritage, while not forgetting traditional values, Calhoun County is tucked away in the Panhandle of Florida. Located just over an hour from Gulf of Mexico. Calhoun County is right in the center of everything Northwest Florida has to offer.

 

To reduce the risk of COVID-19, the Calhoun County Courthouse will be under restricted access until further notice. All County offices are still available by phone, email or through online services. Most courthouse business may be handled in this manner and do not require an in-person visit. A list of County offices and their respective phone numbers are listed below:

Clerk of Court 674-4545
Tax Collector 674-8242
Property Appraiser 674-5636
Supervisor of Elections 674-8568
Building Department 674-4551
Building Official 643-8311
Emergency Management 674-8075
Veteran’s Affairs 674-8305
